24th Session AWS - EC2 Security Groups, NACL


===========================================================================
By default inbound rule are deny and outbound rule are allowed(C.Q)
If you allow any protocol in inbound rule, you no need to allow that on outbound rule = stateful packet inspection(C.Q)
If you allow any protocol in inbound rule, you also need to allow that on outbound rule = stateless packet inspection(C.Q)
===========================================================================
security Group = stateful 
Nacl(network access control list) = stateless

security Group is Ec2 instance level
NACL is subnet(availability zone) level 

